{"title_page": "Albin Ekdal", "text_new": "{{short description|Swedish footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Albin Ekdal\n| image = UEFA EURO qualifiers Sweden vs Spain 20191015 Albin Ekdal 101.jpg\n| image_size = 200\n| caption = Ekdal playing against Spain in 2019\n| fullname = Albin Ekdal\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1989|7|28|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Stockholm]], Sweden\n| height = 1.86 m<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tournament.fifadata.com/documents/FWC/2018/pdf/FWC_2018_SQUADLISTS.PDF |title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia \u2013 List of Players |website=FIFA.com |publisher=F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Football Association |format=PDF |date=4 June 2018 |access-date=19 June 2018}}</ref>\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]]\n| clubnumber = 6\n| youthyears1 = 2005\u20132006\n| youthclubs1 = [[IF Brommapojkarna]]\n| years1 = 2007\u20132008\n| clubs1 = [[IF Brommapojkarna]]\n| caps1 = 24\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2008\u20132010\n| clubs2 = [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]\n| caps2 = 3\n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2009\u20132010\n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[A.C. Siena|Siena]] (loan)\n| caps3 = 26\n| goals3 = 1\n| years4 = 2010\u20132011\n| clubs4 = [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]]\n| caps4 = 22\n| goals4 = 1\n| years5 = 2011\u20132015\n| clubs5 = [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]]\n| caps5 = 114\n| goals5 = 8\n| years6 = 2015\u20132018\n| clubs6 = [[Hamburger SV]]\n| caps6 = 54\n| goals6 = 1\n| years7 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs7 = [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]]\n| caps7 = 54\n| goals7 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2004\u20132006\n| nationalteam1 = [[Sweden national under-17 football team|Sweden U17]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 18\n| nationalgoals1 = 5\n| nationalyears2 = 2007\u20132008\n| nationalteam2 = [[Sweden national under-19 football team|Sweden U19]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 8\n| nationalgoals2 = 2\n| nationalyears3 = 2008\u20132010\n| nationalteam3 = [[Sweden national under-21 football team|Sweden U21]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 12\n| nationalgoals3 = 2\n| nationalyears4 = 2011\u2013\n| nationalteam4 = [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]]\n| nationalcaps4 = 50\n| nationalgoals4 = 0\n| club-update = 13:39, 17 February 2020 (UTC)\n| ntupdate = 15 November 2019\n}}\n'''Albin Ekdal''' ({{IPA-sv|\u02c8\u01cel\u02d0b\u026an \u02c8\u00ea\u02d0kd\u0251\u02d0l}}; born 28 July 1989) is a Swedish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Serie A]] side [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]].\n\nFormed at [[IF Brommapojkarna]], he spent most of his career in Italy, where he made over 200 appearances in [[Serie A]]. He mainly represented [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]], but also played for [[Juventus]], [[A.C. Siena|Siena]], [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]] and [[Sampdoria]] in the competition. He also spent three years in Germany's [[Bundesliga]] with [[Hamburger SV]].\n\nEkdal made his senior international debut for Sweden in 2011. He earned 50 caps for the nation, and represented them at [[UEFA Euro 2016]] and the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Brommapojkarna===\nAlbin Ekdal started his professional playing career with [[IF Brommapojkarna|Brommapojkarna]] at the beginning of the [[2007 Allsvenskan]] season. He played mainly as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]] but also as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] or [[Midfielder#Winger|right midfielder]].\n\n===Juventus===\nOn 23 May 2008, Ekdal signed a four-year contract with [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] of Italy's [[Serie A]].<ref>[http://juventus.com/site/eng/NEWS_newsseriea_3F570B3A13F74B479BAE0E942F34A2A6.asp Albin Ekdal signs 4-year contract with Juventus<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080526181555/http://juventus.com/site/eng/NEWS_newsseriea_3F570B3A13F74B479BAE0E942F34A2A6.asp |date=26 May 2008 }}</ref> He made his Serie A and club debut on 18 October in a 2\u20131 away defeat to [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]], coming on as a substitute in the 75th minute for [[Christian Poulsen]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Al San Paolo Amauri illude la Juve, ora per Ranieri si fa buio pesto |url=https://www.repubblica.it/2008/10/sezioni/sport/calcio/serie_a/giornata-7/napoli-juventus/napoli-juventus.html |accessdate=15 March 2020 |work=La Repubblica |date=18 October 2008 |language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 July 2009, fellow Italian top-flight club [[A.C. Siena|Siena]] signed Ekdal on loan for a season.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Mancini |first1=Riccardo |title=Ekdal in prestito al Siena |url=https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/ufficiale-ekdal-in-prestito-al-siena-161367 |accessdate=15 March 2020 |publisher=Tutto Mercato Web |date=15 July 2009 |language=Italian}}</ref> He made 27 appearances for the [[Tuscany|Tuscans]], who were ultimately relegated at the end of the season, and scored once, in a 4\u20133 loss away to eventual treble winners [[Inter Milan]] on 9 January 2010.<ref>{{cite news |title=Search Results Web results  Serie A: Inter 4-3 Siena |url=https://www.inter.it/en/news/2010/01/9/serie-a-inter-4-3-siena.html |accessdate=15 March 2020 |publisher=Inter Milan |date=9 January 2010}}</ref> \n\nOn 28 June 2010, Juventus sold 50% of their ownership rights of Ekdal to [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]]. As per the deal, the two clubs would agree at the start of each season who would have him as a player.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dn.se/sport/fotboll/albin-ekdal-flyttar-till-bologna|title=Albin Ekdal flyttar till Bologna|date=28 July 2010|work=Dagens Nyheter|accessdate=17 June 2016|language=Swedish}}</ref> He played 23 total games for the ''Rossoblu'' and scored on the anniversary of his last goal, to open a 2\u20130 win at [[AS Bari|Bari]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Ekdal apre, Di Vaio chiude, Il Bari crolla: \u00e8 tutto da rifare |url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/SerieA/Bari/09-01-2011/ekdal-inventa-vaio-chiude-712420464604.shtml |accessdate=15 March 2020 |work=La Gazzetta dello Sport |date=9 January 2011 |language=Italian}}</ref>\n\n===Cagliari===\n[[File:Albin Ekdal 2012.jpg|175px|thumb|Ekdal with [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] in 2012]]\nOn 23 August 2011, Ekdal was sold to fellow Serie A team [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] on a three-year deal for \u20ac3 million.<ref>{{cite news |title=Accordo con la societa' Cagliari Calcio relativo al calciatore Albin Ekdal |url=http://www.juventus.com/media/native/investor-relations-docs/italiano/comunicati/2011/comunicato%2023082011%20ekdal%20ita.pdf |accessdate=15 March 2020 |publisher=Juventus F.C. |date=23 August 2011 |language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 September 2014, Ekdal scored a hat-trick as Cagliari won 4\u20131 at [[Inter Milan]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Inter 1 Cagliari 4: Ekdal hat-trick inspires sensational away win|url=http://www.fourfourtwo.com/sg/news/inter-1-cagliari-4-ekdal-hat-trick-inspires-sensational-away-win|accessdate=28 September 2014|work=[[Four Four Two]]|date=28 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924044949/http://www.fourfourtwo.com/sg/news/inter-1-cagliari-4-ekdal-hat-trick-inspires-sensational-away-win|archive-date=24 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Hamburger SV===\nOn 18 July 2015, German club [[Hamburger SV]] signed Ekdal from Cagliari on a four-year deal for \u20ac4.5 million with wages of \u20ac600,000 per season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hamburg announce Albin Ekdal signing|url=http://www.soccernews.com/hamburg-announce-albin-ekdal-signing/176466/|accessdate=13 August 2015|work=Soccernews|date=18 July 2015}}</ref> He was given the [[Squad number (association football)|number 20 shirt]]. \n\nHe played 57 games for the side in total, who struggled against relegation in each of his three years with the team, ending with their ultimate descent into the [[2018\u201319 2. Bundesliga|2. Bundesliga in 2018]]. He scored once for the team from [[Hamburg]], the only goal of a home win against [[Hertha BSC]] on 5 March 2017.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ekdal gives Hamburg's survival hopes boost; Freiburg edge Eintracht |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/german-bundesliga/story/3075849/albin-ekdal-gives-hamburgs-survival-hopes-boost-and-freiburg-edge-eintracht-frankfurt |accessdate=15 March 2020 |agency=PA Sport |publisher=ESPN FC |date=5 March 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 January 2017, Ekdal received the first [[Penalty card#Red_card|red card]] of his career, after 33 minutes of a 1\u20130 loss at [[VfL Wolfsburg]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Fredriksson |first1=Emelie |last2=J\u00f6nsson |first2=Fredrik |title=Albin Ekdal fick karri\u00e4rens f\u00f6rsta r\u00f6da kort |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/MllpK/albin-ekdal-fick-karriarens-forsta-roda-kort |accessdate=15 March 2020 |language=Swedish|work=Aftonbladet}}</ref>\n\n===Sampdoria===\nOn 14 August 2018, following Hamburg's relegation from the Bundesliga, Ekdal returned to Serie A by signing for [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sampdoria.it/en/ekdal-arrives-from-hamburg-on-a-permanent-deal/|title=Ekdal arrives from Hamburg on a permanent deal|last=|first=|date=16 August 2018|publisher=U.C. Sampdoria|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n[[File:UEFA EURO qualifiers Sweden vs Spain 20191015 Albin Ekdal and Pierre Bengtsson.jpg|thumb|Ekdal (right) and [[Pierre Bengtsson]] playing against [[Spain national football team|Spain]] in October 2019]]\nEkdal made his debut for [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]] on 10 August 2011 in a friendly game away to [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]] in [[Kharkiv]]. He came on as a 60th-minute substitute for [[Sebastian Larsson]] in a 1\u20130 win.\n\nEkdal was named in Sweden's 23-man squad for [[UEFA Euro 2016]] in France, despite a deep cut in his back from celebrating Hamburg's recent Bundesliga survival putting his involvement at risk.<ref>{{cite news |title=Injury doubt Ekdal included in Sweden's Euro 2016 squad |url=https://www.goal.com/en-ae/news/ekdal-included-in-swedens-euro-2016-squad/o6pojxiyz3ar10x5cdatk4nv5 |accessdate=15 March 2020 |publisher=Goal |date=12 May 2016}}</ref> He played each match as the Swedes came bottom of their group.\n\nIn June 2018 Ekdal was named in Sweden's 23-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Crawford |first1=Stephen |title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad - Final 23-man lists |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb |website=Goal |accessdate=16 July 2019 |date=4 June 2018}}</ref> He played all five games of a run to the quarter-finals.\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is the son of [[Lennart Ekdal]], an award-winning Swedish journalist, TV personality and newscaster known for his work for the newspaper ''[[Dagens Nyheter]]'' and the financial magazine ''[[Veckans Aff\u00e4rer]]'', as well as hosting TV shows such as ''Kalla fakta'', ''Halvtid f\u00f6r Reinfeldt'', ''Kv\u00e4lls\u00f6ppet med Ekdal & Hakelius'' and ''Hetluft''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv4.se/1.290538/2008/02/27/lennart_ekdal_prisad_for_sin_journalistik|title=Lennart Ekdal prisad f\u00f6r sin journalistik \u2013 Kv\u00e4lls\u00f6ppet \u2013 tv4.se|accessdate=17 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120223114658/http://www.tv4.se/1.290538/2008/02/27/lennart_ekdal_prisad_for_sin_journalistik|archive-date=23 February 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mobil.sr.se/site/index.aspx?groupid=3803&artikel=1772070&unitID=83 |title=Sveriges Radio \u2013 Sidan finns ej |publisher= |accessdate=17 June 2016 }}{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nEkdal's younger brother, [[Hjalmar Ekdal]], is also a professional footballer who plays for Swedish first tier club [[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby IF]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Hjalmar Ekdal vill g\u00e5 i brorsans fotsp\u00e5r|language=Swedish|date=15 July 2014|accessdate=11 June 2017|publisher=[[Expressen]]|url=http://www.expressen.se/gt/sport/hjalmar-ekdal-vill-ga-i-brorsans-fotspar/}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March 2020, Ekdal tested positive for [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]], amid its [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|pandemic in Italy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sampdoria.it/en/covid-19-sampdoria-statement-13-march-2020/|title=COVID-19: Sampdoria statement, 13 March 2020|last=|first=|website=U.C. Sampdoria|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|date=13 March 2020|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 8 February 2020}}<ref name=\"sw\">{{Soccerway|21090}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!rowspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA|Europe]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[IF Brommapojkarna|Brommapojkarna]]\n|[[2007 Allsvenskan|2007]]\n|[[Allsvenskan]]\n|15||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||15||0\n|-\n|[[2008 Superettan|2008]]\n|[[Superettan]]\n|9||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||9||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!24!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!24!!0\n|-\n|[[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]\n|[[2008\u201309 Serie A|2008\u201309]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Serie A]]\n|3||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||3||0\n|-\n|[[Robur Siena|Siena]] (loan)\n|[[2009\u201310 Serie A|2009\u201310]]\n|26||1||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||27||1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]\n|[[2010\u201311 Serie A|2010\u201311]]\n|0||0||0||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||1||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!3!!0!!0!!0!!1!!0!!0!!0!!4!!0\n|-\n|[[Bologna F.C.|Bologna]]\n|[[2010\u201311 Serie A|2010\u201311]]\n|rowspan=\"5\"|Serie A\n|22||1||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||23||1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Cagliar